1159	\begin{proof}
1160	  \uses{thm:Scheme_basicOpenCover_finset_inf_isLocalization, def:Scheme_IsCechAcyclicCover, thm:Scheme_cechCohomology_subsingleton_of_cechCochain_exactAt, def:Scheme_splitEpi_pi_lift_of_injective}
1161	  \leanok
1162	  The classical proof proceeds in four steps.
1163	
1164	  \textbf{Step~1: Reduction to per-generator local exactness.} Since $s$ generates the unit ideal, exactness of a map of $\mathcal O_X(U)$-modules is a local property at the cover $\{D(f)\}_{f \in s}$. It suffices to prove exactness after localizing at each generator $f \in s$.
1165	
1166	  \textbf{Step~2: Identification of the localized complex.} Localizing at $f$ identifies the factor at $(f_0,\dots,f_n)$ with $\mathcal O_X(U)[1/(f f_0 \cdots f_n)]$. Reassembling, the localized Čech complex is naturally isomorphic to the Čech complex of $D(f)$ with respect to the restricted cover $\{D(f) \cap D(f')\}_{f' \in s}$. Concretely, the formalisation of this step uses four Mathlib API pieces in sequence. Writing $V_x = \bigcap_{a} D(x_a)$ for a tuple $x : \{0,\dots,n\} \to s_0$:
1167	  \begin{enumerate}
1168	    \item[(i)] \emph{Image-Finset bridge.} The categorical product $\prod^c_a D(x_a)$ in the lattice of opens coincides with the $\inf'$ of $D$ along the image $x(\{0,\dots,n\}) \subseteq s_0$. Mathlib's \texttt{Finset.inf\_univ\_eq\_iInf}, \texttt{Finset.inf'\_eq\_inf}, and \texttt{Finset.inf'\_image}, framed by a \texttt{le\_antisymm} step using the projection \texttt{Pi.\!$\pi$} and the canonical lift \texttt{Pi.lift}, identify these. (The direct route via a \texttt{CompleteLattice.finite\_product\_eq\_finset\_inf} fails on universe grounds: the index type $\mathrm{Fin}(n+1) : \mathrm{Type}_0$ and the open-set type $\mathrm{Opens} : \mathrm{Type}_u$ are not in the same universe.)
1169	    \item[(ii)] \emph{Restriction-of-section identity.} $V_x \cap D(f) = D(f|_{V_x})$, where $f|_{V_x}$ denotes the image of $f$ under the presheaf restriction $\mathcal O_X(U) \to \mathcal O_X(V_x)$. This is Mathlib's \texttt{Scheme.basicOpen\_res}.
1170	    \item[(iii)] \emph{Per-coord \texttt{IsLocalization.Away}.} Each $V_x$ is affine by (i) combined with Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_basicOpenCover_finset_inf_isAffineOpen}. Composing (i)–(ii) with \texttt{IsAffineOpen.isLocalization\_of\_eq\_basicOpen} then certifies
1171	    \[
1172	      \mathcal O_X(V_x \cap D(f)) \;=\; \mathcal O_X(V_x)\bigl[1/(f|_{V_x})\bigr]
1173	    \]
1174	    as an \texttt{IsLocalization.Away} algebra structure, with algebra map the presheaf restriction $\mathcal O_X(V_x) \to \mathcal O_X(V_x \cap D(f))$. Compare also Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_basicOpenCover_finset_inf_isLocalization} for the ambient $\inf'$-form.
1175	    \item[(iv)] \emph{Finite-product localization lift.} The per-coord \texttt{IsLocalization.Away} structures of (iii) are upgraded to \texttt{IsLocalizedModule} instances via the adapter
1176	    \texttt{instIsLocalizedModuleTo\-LinearMap\-To\-AlgHom\-Of\-IsLocalization\-AlgebraMap\-Submonoid} (in \textsf{Mathlib.Algebra.Module.LocalizedModule.IsLocalization}). The finite-product packaging \texttt{IsLocalizedModule.pi} (in \textsf{Mathlib.RingTheory.TensorProduct.IsBaseChangePi}) then assembles these into a single \texttt{IsLocalizedModule\,(Submonoid.powers $f$)} instance on the cochain-degree product $\prod_x \mathcal O_X(V_x)$.
1177	  \end{enumerate}
1178	  With (i)–(iv) in hand, the $K_0$-level exactness $h_{a_0\text{-fun}}(f)$ established earlier transports along the two-row ladder built from \texttt{IsLocalizedModule.iso} on each summand $\mathrm{LocalizedModule}(\langle f \rangle)\,(K_0)_i \;\simeq_R\; M'_i$, where $M'_i$ is the slice-cover summand at degree $i$, via \texttt{Function.Exact.iff\_of\_ladder\_linearEquiv}. This yields the localized exactness at coordinate $f$ that Step~4 consumes. The split-epi reduction of Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_splitEpi_pi_lift_of_injective} enters at the cochain-degree-$0$ end of the ladder so that the augmented complex's $K_{-1}$-term threads through.
1179	
1180	  \textbf{Step~3: Contraction by extra degeneracy.} In the cover of $D(f)$, the member indexed by $f' = f$ is $D(f)$ itself. The augmented Čech complex therefore admits a section: map a family to its component at $f$. This section extends to an extra degeneracy on the augmented simplicial object, exhibiting the augmented Čech complex as contractible. Consequently the complex is exact in all positive degrees.
1181	
1182	  \textbf{Step~4: Globalization.} Each localized differential is exact, so the unlocalized differential is exact by the local-to-global principle for spanning sets. Hence $\check H^n(\mathfrak U, \mathcal O_X) = 0$ for $n \ge 1$.
1183	\end{proof}
